* Contents:
============

* What does the program do?
============================

The program demonstrates the use of fork() together with execlp().

The main program calls fork() three times. Each time, the child process
is replaced using execlp() with an external program called "iden".

Each child process executes only the "iden" program, which prints the
identifiers of the process that executes it (UID, GID, PID, PPID, PGID).

In the main program, the parent process waits for all child processes
to finish using three calls to wait(). After all children terminate,
the parent process prints its own process identifiers.

The execlp() function uses:
- argv[1]: path to the "iden" executable (provided via Makefile)
- argv[2]: name of the "iden" program

* How to run the program:
=========================

1. Compile the project:
   make

   This compiles both source files (execlp.c and iden.c).

2. Run the program:
   make run

   This executes the program and passes the required arguments automatically.
